---
title: Pancetta Flatbread Pizzas with Shredded Brussels Sprouts and a Chili Honey Drizzle
description: Brussels sprouts may get a bad rap, but anyone who still believes the naysaying hasn’t had them properly. Just look at this recipe: it’s a Brussels sprout pizza. How could it possibly go wrong? Pre-cut shreds of the brassica are sprinkled on top and allowed to get nice and crispy as they bake. And just to make sure there’s no shortage of awesome, there’s also a good sprinkling of cheese, porky pancetta cubes, and an addictive spicy honey drizzle.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/pancetta-flatbread-pizzas-5b58cf2e.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/pancetta-flatbread-pizzas-df1e5b17.pdf
nutrition:
  calories: 630 kcal
  fat: 25 g
  saturated fat: 10 g
  carbohydrates: 77 g
  sugar: 13 g
  protein: 28 g
  fiber: 8 g
  sodium: 1210 mg
time required: 20 minutes
cuisine: North America
course: main course
servings: 2
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/pancetta-flatbread-pizzas-59f24fd6ae702a4c8d665f12
author: Sara Heilman
---

Place @flatbreads{2%unit} on a lightly oiled #baking sheet{}. Adjust oven rack to upper position. Place flatbreads in oven, then turn on oven and preheat to 475 degrees. Once flatbreads are lightly toasted, about ~{7%minutes} later, remove from oven and set aside, leaving oven on to continue heating.

Heat a drizzle of @vegetable oil{} in a large pan over medium-high heat. Add half the @pancetta{2%ounce} (use the rest as you like) and cook until it releases a little bit of grease, ~{1-2%minutes}. Toss in @shredded Brussels sprouts{8%ounce} and another drizzle of oil. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Cook, tossing, until lightly crisped, about ~{5%minutes}.

Meanwhile, place half the @whole peeled tomatoes{7%ounce} in a #medium bowl{} and break up with your hands until you have no pieces larger than ½ inch (use the rest of the tomatoes as you like). Season with salt, pepper, and half the @Italian seasoning{1%tablespoon}.

Spread tomatoes over flatbreads, then sprinkle evenly with @Italian cheese blend{1%cup}. Season with salt, pepper, and remaining Italian seasoning. Top with Brussels sprout and pancetta mixture.

Bake pizzas in oven until crust is golden brown, cheese is melted, and toppings are lightly crisped, ~{5-7%minutes}. Meanwhile, combine @honey{½%ounce} and @chili flakes{1%teaspoon}(to taste) in a #small bowl{}.

Drizzle pizzas with honey mixture. Cut into slices and serve.

> Brussels sprouts may get a bad rap, but anyone who still believes the naysaying hasn't had them properly. Just look at this recipe: it's a Brussels sprout pizza. How could it possibly go wrong?